---
description: Supabase with SvelteKit (SSR cookies, safe env)
globs:
  - "src/**/*"
---

- Use `@supabase/supabase-js` v2 and `@supabase/ssr` for cookie-based auth on SSR.
- Client-side: create a Supabase client in `+layout.js`.
- Server: in `+layout.server.js` or actions/endpoints, access the session via SSR helpers; never expose the service role key to the client.
- Env:
  - Client: `PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` via `$env/static/public`.
  - Server: secrets via `$env/static/private` or `$env/dynamic/private`.
- Prefer actions (`+page.server.js`) for mutations; use endpoints for API-style responses.
